[2026-05-18T15:14:37.412Z] [TOOL_RESULT] 1	# Task: 02-design-system/005-generate-design-references
2	
3	# Generate Design Reference HTML
4	
5	Generate project-specific HTML design mockups that serve as reference examples for `stitch-generate` when building all screens in `03-build-screens`.
6	
7	## Why
8	
9	The `stitch-generate` skill matches new screens against reference examples to produce consistent HTML. By generating project-specific references that embody our design system, every screen generated in `03-build-screens` will inherit the correct visual language — which then converts cleanly to Flutter widgets.
10	
11	## Steps
12	
13	1. **Read inputs** — Load `.stitch/system/DESIGN.md`, `.stitch/screens.json`, and `.stitch/UX.md`
14	
15	2. **Select 3 representative screens** from `screens.json`:
16	   - **Single Screen** — the most typical/common screen (e.g., a main content list or primary feature screen)
17	   - **Multi-State** — a screen with multiple interaction states (e.g., form with empty/filling/complete states, or a list with loading/empty/populated)
18	   - **Celebration** — an achievement or milestone screen (e.g., goal reached, streak milestone, completion)
19	
20	3. **Create `.stitch/system/META.md`** following this format:
21	   ```markdown
22	   # {App Name}
23	
24	   - **App Type:** {category}
25	   - **Tags:** {comma-separated keywords}
26	   - **Platform:** Mobile (375px base width)
27	   - **Interaction Density:** {Low | Medium | High}
28	   - **Target Framework:** Flutter (Material 3)
29	
30	   ## Screens
31	
32	   | File | Pattern | Description |
33	   |------|---------|-------------|
34	   | `single-screen.html` | Single Screen | {what it shows} |
35	   | `multi-state-screen.html` | Multi-State | {what states it covers} |
36	   | `celebration-screen.html` | Celebration | {what achievement it shows} |
37	
38	   ## Key Patterns
39	
40	   - {notable UI pattern 1}
41	   - {notable UI pattern 2}
42	   ```
43	
44	4. **Generate each HTML file** using `stitch-generate`:
45	   - Each file must be self-contained (embedded `<style>`, inline SVG icons, Google Fonts via `<link>`)
46	   - CSS custom properties in `:root` for all design tokens from DESIGN.md
47	   - Semantic HTML (`<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<section>`)
48	   - ARIA attributes on interactive elements
49	   - `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` block
50	   - Phone frame wrapper (`.phone` at 375px for mobile)
51	
52	## Output
53	
54	```
55	.stitch/system/
56	├── DESIGN.md              (created by task 002)
57	├── META.md
58	├── single-screen.html
59	├── multi-state-screen.html
60	└── celebration-screen.html
61	```
